Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 18:35:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [OpenMP] Generate libomp headers locally when split

When OpenMP is built standalone against an installed LLVM tree,
LIBOMP_HEADERS_INTDIR can point at the installed LLVM resource include
directory instead of the local runtime build directory. That makes GCC
pick up Clang's full resource include directory while compiling libomp.

Only use the LLVM resource include directory in the bootstrapping runtimes
path. Standalone runtimes builds should generate omp.h and omp-tools.h
locally.
---
 openmp/runtime/src/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/openmp/runtime/src/CMakeLists.txt b/openmp/runtime/src/CMakeLists.txt
index c224a10eb1ef..c6ad5095fd53 100644
--- a/openmp/runtime/src/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/openmp/runtime/src/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@ include(ExtendPath)
 
 # The generated headers will be placed in clang's resource if using it to
 # compile openmp in a runtimes-bootstrapping build.
-if(LLVM_TREE_AVAILABLE AND LLVM_RUNTIMES_BUILD)
+if(LLVM_TREE_AVAILABLE AND LLVM_RUNTIMES_BUILD AND HAVE_LLVM_LIT)
   set(LIBOMP_HEADERS_INTDIR ${LLVM_BINARY_DIR}/${LIBOMP_HEADERS_INSTALL_PATH})
 else()
   set(LIBOMP_HEADERS_INTDIR ${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR})
